Privacy Policy
This Privacy Policy shall apply to the applications published in the Apple App Store by AnyDay Apps (“OnPhone,” “we,” “us,” or “our”) and that
            are accessible from mobile devices and personal computers (the "App"), and the use of the websites controlled
            by AnyDay Apps in general (the "Website"; App, and Website together the "Services").
Overview
This Privacy Policy describes how OnPhone treats information that it collects and receives related to your use of OnPhone’s products, services, and websites. Our primary goal in collecting information is to provide and improve our products and services.
Children’s Personal Information
All OnPhone products, services and websites are not intended for children under the age of 13, so children under the age of 13 should not use them at any time.
OnPhone does not knowingly collect any information from children under the age of 13. In the event that OnPhone discovers that it has received personal information from a child under the age of 13, OnPhone will promptly delete such personal information in a secure manner.
Information OnPhone Collects and Uses
OnPhone collects information when you use and access OnPhone’s products, services and website. We categorize the information we collect into three categories (collectively referred to as “Customer Information”): Personal Information, App Data and Share Data.
Must be clear that end user’s personal info will not be shared or sold to third parties for the purpose of marketing. For example - ‘No mobile information will be shared with third parties/affiliates for marketing/promotional purposes. All the above categories exclude text messaging originator opt-in data and consent; this information will not be shared with any third parties.’
“Personal Information” is information about you that is personally identifiable, including your full name, business or residential address, email address, land-line or existing mobile phone number, or billing information.
“App Data” is information about the nature of your usage of OnPhone’s website and products and services and non-personal information. App Data can include: IP addresses, domain servers, referring/exit pages, operating system information, unique device identifiers, such as UDID and/or Ethernet MAC address, date/time stamp, clickstream data and information about actions taken by you through interaction with OnPhone’s products and/or advertising displayed within OnPhone products, messages sent and received using OnPhone services, information about those messages (date, duration, recipients, size, attachments), type of device, location information, age, gender, type of web browser, one or more cookies that identify your browser, and telecommunications carrier information.
“Share Data” is data and information you provide for use with OnPhone’s products or services, such as text, audio, and photos you make available through the Apps or contacts you add or import for use with OnPhone products, and which may be made available to third parties by your actions when using OnPhone products or services.
Information Sharing and Disclosure
OnPhone uses Customer Information to enhance your use of the OnPhone services by processing such information for various purposes, including improving and providing OnPhone’s products and services, product notifications, delivering advertisements and related links, for sending, sharing and storing your Share Data as you direct through use of OnPhone products and services, and other purposes relating to offering you OnPhone products and services.
If you provide your phone number as part of a request for information about OnPhone products or services or in setting up an account, we may use that phone number and share that phone number with third parties to contact you about OnPhone products and services and to provide advertisements to you about OnPhone Products and services.
OnPhone does not rent, sell, or share any Customer Information except as provided above and unless: you initiate the sharing through the OnPhone products, services or website; you have provided your express consent; and in the following circumstances:
(i) OnPhone may engage a trusted third party to perform limited functions on our behalf, such as fulfilling newsletter subscriptions, sending requested postal mail and e-mail, SMS, MMS, and voice communications, analyzing and processing data (such as billing information), and providing customer service. We require that these parties agree to use such information in a confidential manner. These third parties may have access to Personal Information needed to perform their functions, but we do not permit them to use it for other purposes.
(ii) OnPhone may share App Data and certain aggregated, non-personal information with third parties, but such information does not include your name, email address or any other Personal Information.
(iii) OnPhone may share Customer Information to respond to legal requirements, when legally required to do so, or at the request of governmental authorities.
(iv) OnPhone may share Customer Information to verify or enforce compliance with user agreements and applicable laws, to protect against fraud, to detect and prevent security or technical issues, to protect against misuse or unauthorized use of the OnPhone products, services, computing systems, or website, or to protect against imminent harm to the rights, property or safety of OnPhone, its subscribers or the public.
(v) OnPhone may share Customer Information with a successor entity or in connection with a corporate merger, consolidation, sale of assets or other corporate reorganization provided that use of Customer Information is in compliance with this Privacy Policy.
(vi) OnPhone may share your Customer Information with a third party if you have consented to receive information from that third party through OnPhone products or services. Such third parties will handle, store, retain and access such user information in accordance with the terms and conditions of their agreements with you, if any, as well as their own privacy policies and as authorized and agreed upon by you as part of agreements for use of our products and services. It is your responsibility to carefully review such agreements and privacy policies. You acknowledge that OnPhone shall have no liability to you for sharing of such information to such third parties as authorized by you and OnPhone disclaims any and all liability relating thereto. If OnPhone desires to use Personal Information for any purposes other than those described in this Privacy Policy, we will offer you the opportunity to opt out of such use for those other purposes.
Cookies and Tracking
When you visit OnPhone or use OnPhone applications, we may send cookies to your computer that uniquely identify your browser or use tracking pixels, agents or other visitor identification technology (collectively, “Tags”) that collect App Data. We may also include Tags in promotional materials in order to determine whether messages have been opened and acted upon.
We use and share App Data as provided above.
Most browsers allow you to disable cookies or set your browser to alert you when cookies are being sent to your computer. If you disable cookies, you may not be able to utilize certain OnPhone products and services.
We use analytics tools provided by Google, Facebook, Flurry, Adjust, Braze, Qonversion and Crashlytics (“Analytics Tools”) which also use Tags to collect and analyze information about your use of our desktop and mobile applications. We use Analytics Tools to collect App Data, which we use as provided above. That information is also used by the Analytics Tools providers according to their privacy policies.
