Currently, we do not respond to “Do Not Track” browser features.
Security and Data Integrity
We have physical, electronic, and procedural safeguards to protect the loss, misuse, and alteration of the Customer Information under our control. Customer Information we collect is stored in a secure manner that is accessible only by authorized OnPhone personnel, contractors, and agents bound by confidentiality obligations and is only disclosed under the provisions of this Privacy Policy. Our processing of Personal Information is only for the purposes for which it was collected and in accordance with this Privacy Policy. Periodically, OnPhone undertakes a review of its privacy practices to ensure that that the information we collect is needed to provide or improve the services we provide.
Links to Third Party Sites
As a convenience to you, we may provide links and/or connections to third-party web sites or services from within our website or our products or services. OnPhone is not responsible for the privacy practices or content of these third-party sites.
Access/Removal of Your Personal Information
If you want us to remove your Personal Information from our database, or would like to access the Personal Information we have that was collected from you, you can contact us using the contact information provided below. Certain of our products and services require the use of App Data and such data is retained by OnPhone and used as described in this Privacy Policy.
Modifications of Privacy Policy
OnPhone reserves the right, at our discretion, to change, update or modify this Privacy Policy at any time by posting such change, update or modification on the OnPhone website and in the app stores from which Apps are made available. Any such change, update or modification will be effective immediately upon notice, which OnPhone may provide by any means, including, without limitation, posting on the OnPhone website, notifications within OnPhone applications, or electronic mail. Your continued use of the OnPhone website and/or any OnPhone products and services following the posting of changes will mean you accept those changes. Use of information that we gather is subject to the Privacy Policy in effect at the time of use.
Contact Us
If you have any questions or concerns regarding this Privacy Policy, please send us an email at
support@anydayapps.com
or write to us at Anyday Apps, Inc. 1007 North Orange Street 4th Floor Ste 57, Wilmington, DE 19801, United States. If we receive formal privacy-related complaints, it is our policy to use reasonable efforts to communicate with the complaining party about its concerns to resolve privacy complaints.
Privacy Notice
SOME USEFUL DATA PRIVACY FACTS FROM YOUR FRIENDS AT ONPHONE
We’ve provided this Privacy Notice to help you understand how Anyday Apps, Inc. (“OnPhone,” “we,” “us,” or “our”) collects and uses personal information and, for California residents, to inform them of the categories of personal information we collect and the purposes for which the categories of personal information will be used, as required under the California Consumer Privacy Act of 2018 (“CCPA”).
The technologies we use process data for our products and services are complicated, but this Privacy Notice is meant to provide you with an easy-to-understand overview of the categories of personal information we collect, why we collect them, and how we use them. While this Privacy Notice provides a general overview, for a complete understanding about what personal information we gather and how we use it, please review our
Privacy Policy
and
Terms of Service
. Also, please review our “Notice of Financial Incentive” included below.
What does OnPhone do?
OnPhone offers software applications for iOS and Android mobile devices (and limited versions of those applications for internet-connected desktop computers), that enable end users to send SMS and MMS communications as well as to place or receive calls. OnPhone licenses its applications to U.S.-based end users for use in the U.S. OnPhone’s Canadian subsidiary, Dinopilot, offers the some of the same applications and functionality in limited markets outside of the U.S. If you’re an end user licensed by Dinopilot, references to “OnPhone,” “we,” “us,” or “our” in this Privacy Notice mean Dinopilot.
OnPhone’s mobile applications are: “OnPhone,” “OnPhone App” (collectively, the “Apps”). The Apps are available in iOS and/or Android versions for tablets and smartphones and are distributed through Apple’s “App Store” and the “Google Play” store (collectively, “App Stores”). OnPhone are supported by advertising revenue and are free to use, with certain additional features available for purchase, including a “Remove Ads” feature that allows end users to purchase a subscription for an ad-free version.
OnPhone Apps provide end users with access to a OnPhone-supplied phone number that becomes associated with an end user’s account. Receiving and sending SMS and MMS messages through the OnPhone Apps are paid to users as are inbound calls. However, placing outbound calls requires end users to either purchase license credits for outbound calling through App Stores, or earn license credits for outbound calling by viewing video ads (each ad view typically equates to one minute of license credits) or completing third party offers.
What personal information does OnPhone need to use?
In order for inbound or outbound calls and messages to work for our OnPhone Apps, we need basic information about the sender and the recipient, namely their phone numbers. We also need to know how to associate all those calls and messages with a specific account for those Apps, so we require you to provide some basic information during signup. That’s how we can make sure that calls and messages are connected correctly. That information is required in order for us to provide our services, so please keep that in mind when deciding whether to use our Apps.
Since our OnPhone Apps are supported by advertising, we -like other ad-supported companies (e.g. Facebook) – gather information about you, your mobile device from the OnPhone Apps, and your use of OnPhone Apps. That information is shared with Advertising Companies who process it and match it with other data and use algorithms to serve ads that are more relevant to you. That’s basically how we, and others, make money to support and offer OnPhone Apps for free.
Can I opt out of the sale of my personal information?
Under the California Consumer Privacy Act (“CCPA”), provision of personal information to our advertising service providers may constitute a “sale” of that information, so for CCPA purposes, we consider that we “sell” your personal information to deliver ads in our OnPhone Apps. If you don’t like that personal information is used to deliver ads to you in our OnPhone Apps, then you can opt out by purchasing a “Remove Ads” subscription from the applicable Apps Stores, which you may do within the “settings” feature of your OnPhone App.
NOTICE OF FINANCIAL INCENTIVE:
If you’re a California resident, you should know that the “Remove Ads” feature is offered in compliance with Section 1798.125(a)(2) of the CCPA which allows us to charge a fee if we can’t generate any advertising revenue from your use of the OnPhone Apps. That fee is a good faith estimate of the value of the advertising revenue for a typical user of the OnPhone Apps as determined by an industry standard calculation of lifetime value of a user who views our ads as compared to the lifetime value of a typical user who purchases “Remove Ads.”
When you purchase a “Remove Ads” subscription, we stop providing your personal information to Advertising Companies, but you have to maintain that subscription in order to prevent the use of your personal information for advertising purposes. If you wish to cancel your “Remove Ads” subscription as a financial incentive to not have your Personal Information sold, you will have to do so from the Apple or Google Play store. If you cancel or let the “Remove Ads” subscription lapse, then your personal information will be used for advertising in the OnPhone Apps and, by allowing the subscription to lapse, you are expressly consenting to our use of your personal information for advertising within the OnPhone Apps.
Remember that purchasing a “Remove Ads” subscription for OnPhone Apps is the only way for you to opt out of our sale of your personal information if you still want to use our OnPhone Apps.
Contacts Permission Request
OnPhone accesses your contacts to allow you to easily call and text with your friends and family.
OnPhone collects numbers and names of your contacts to let you enjoy calling and texting with those who are also using our app by auto-matching phone numbers from contacts.
Your contacts wii be encrypted, uploaded and securely stored in the OnPhone Server and will never be shared with 3rd parties. You can delete these data by deactivating the account or contacting us.
What categories of third parties does OnPhone engage?
While OnPhone maintains its own data servers for the core data management for the Apps, we engage third parties to provide other services, as follows: (i) .”Backend Providers” provide the backend transmission systems necessary for the Apps to function and include local exchange carriers connected to the PSTN (Public Switch Telephone Network) who connect communications for us, data backhaul providers who transfer data across the continent, and hosting providers; (ii) “Service Providers” who provide analytics, calendar, user notification, and related business services and customer support platforms; and (iii) “Advertising Companies” who provide advertising services for our OnPhone Apps. We have contractual agreements with those third parties that limit the use of personal information for the specific purpose identified in those agreements.
